Patch Set 2:

John, so would I. Any good suggestions how to test that would be greatly appreciated.

Patch Set 2:

Looking at the equivalent v1 code (glance/registry/client/v1/api.py) I see a v1 'def configure_registry_client()' but it is not called in the v1 get_registry_client function.

I would like to understand if it makes sense (or not) for v2 to take the same approach as v1 -- ie not call configure_registry_client at this point in get_registry_client.

Thanks.

Patch Set 2:

The approach seems to be little bit different between v1 and v2. The registry is imported in v1/images.py from glance.registry.client.v1.api and in Controller __init__ the configure_registry_client() gets called.

v2/images.py does not have import for any glance.registry.client and it's also not called there (nor anywhere else at the moment).

As the function does not take any parameters and it just creates 3 global variables I'm not sure where it actually would be best to be called. for clarity I'd like to see it called in the registry/vX/api.py (same file it sits in) but I think which ever way we decide to go, it should be consistent between v1 and v2. Is there some specific reason why this should not be called at get_registry_client?

Regardless where it gets called, I would like to get some input how to test that. One option would be to call it in the get_registry_client and remove the calls for it from the tests/unit/vX/test_registry_client.py, which would solve our testing issue as well.

Patch Set 2:

> Is there some specific reason why this should not be called at get_registry_client?

I wonder if that means we could be calling the configure function multiple times when (as per v1) it only needs to be called once?
